    <restriction base="string">
      <enumeration value="barrage">
        <annotation>
          <documentation>barrier across a stream provided with a series of gates or other control mechanisms to control the water-surface level upstream, to regulate the flow or to divert water supplies into a canal.
&lt;i&gt;(Source: barrage. (2010). In International Glossary of Hydrology Online.Retrieved May 5, 2010, from http://webworld.unesco.org/water/ihp/db/glossary/glu/EN/GF0110EN.HTM)&lt;/i&gt;</documentation>
